think that generated updates should be preserved. If the agent modifies build.gradle or creates a new version directory, it should definitely include opens. Maybe I should take an advisory approach if any guidance is needed for the agent.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering native library risks**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the potential risks related to the Conscrypt library. Since it’s JNI-backed, native-image failures are likely due to metadata or resource configuration issues rather than external services being missing. I also need to be aware that extracting native libraries requires executable temp space; I should only set `org.conscrypt.native.workdir` if there's a local failure referencing noexec. Additionally, warnings may arise from Native Image or JDK 25 regarding future System.load calls, so I need to verify locally.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency or Docker service is needed; the uber artifact has no declared dependencies and embeds its native libraries, but meaningful socket/channel coverage needs JVM/native-image module opens already present in the existing scaffold.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Use Conscrypt directly via `Conscrypt.newProvider()` or explicit provider selection; no external server is required because meaningful TLS/SSLEngine coverage can use in-memory handshakes or loopback sockets. Preserve/add the existing test and native-image build arguments `--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED`, `--add-opens=java.base/java.net=ALL-UNNAMED`, and `--add-opens=java.base/sun.nio.ch=ALL-UNNAMED` when covering socket wrapping, channel-backed sockets, or file-descriptor paths. Do not set `org.conscrypt.native.workdir` unless local execution reports that the temp directory is mounted `noexec`.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Conscrypt is JNI-backed and extracts `META-INF/native/libconscrypt_openjdk_jni-*` from the uber 